  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: In some cases, when app is closed by pressing back button and then opened again, the layout is broken. Also, when I click on the screen Android App Info (Android Settings) app is opened. The only way to get out of it is to kill the app and open it again. \r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7532782/39807017-9571b51c-537b-11e8-9154-9e9037d39841.png\" width=\"200\">\r\n\r\nAnother example:\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7532782/39807029-a00e9ac6-537b-11e8-8621-6c7c4394ab61.png\" width=\"200\">\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nApp is restored to the most recent screen when it's opened from the background.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nWhen app is opened from the background, the layout is broken and any click opens Android Settings app.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open Status on Android\r\n- Go to Profile\r\n- Click share contact code\r\n- Press device back button and exit the app\r\n- Open list of apps in the background and restore Status  \r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: nightly, May 9\r\n* Operating System: Android\r\n* It does not happen every time back button is pressed. I.e. closing the app by pressing back button in Home screen works fine",
